snippet.textDisplay:
Get some Purell, Ben.
I worked in Beijing China in 1987-8. Filthy place. Air stunk of cinder ash; Chinese people have very bad oral hygiene and bad breath. The restaurants' dish ware often had a greasy film on it, like the plate was washed with cold water. There was no toilet paper in the factories and some business offices! Everyone had a handkerchief....

Cut to 2002, when I started going to Hong Kong. Cleaner than the north, but still not the cleanest of cultures, because too many people, many of the poor.

This is what spreads disease - filth and poverty.

Do Not Panic. Take a bath, frequently, and brush your teeth. China has come around and people are more focused on hygiene than the late 80's. But still, considering their diet, many smokers, and questionable oral health practices, well.... no kissy kissy these days.
